USX Corp said it and WorthingtonIndustries &lt;WTHG.O> Inc's Worthingon Specialty Products steelprocessing plant in Jackson, Mich., has recently reachedproduction at the levels for which it was designed.    The company said the 600,000 short ton per year plant isdesigned to provide automotive, appliance and other customerswith first-stage processed steel for just-in-time delivery.    It opened in August 1986, just as USX was beginning asix-month labor dispute. USX is sourcing the plant with coilsfrom its Gary, Ind., works and Mon Valley Works nearPittsburgh, and Worthington is operating the plant. Reuter&#3;